<p>Metro DC DSA Weekly Update for Friday, February 21, 2020
</p>
## <p>THE WEEKEND 
</p>
<p>This weekend, important canvasses for the Super Tuesday Virginia Primary (see DSA for Bernie, below), as well as action for our endorsed local candidates <a href="https://www.janeese4dc.com/">Janeese Lewis George</a> in DC Ward 4, <a href="https://www.mobilize.us/janeese4dc/event/232242/">a rally and canvass Sunday</a> and <a href="https://www.meetup.com/mdcdsa/events/267883893/">planning meeting Monday</a> and Mckayla Wilkes in Maryland‚Äôs Fifth C.D., canvasses (Saturday and Sunday) and text parties; more <a href="https://m.facebook.com/events/491967594934547">here</a> and <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeB71coX5dKCzihm7gUisz2j19hkCvMhoIgdS65TYm2FRRyHw/viewform">here</a>. 
</p><br><br>
<p>EARLY NEXT WEEK an important collaboration with allies: The DC Tenants Union will be doing a <a href="https://www.meetup.com/mdcdsa/events/268828938/">special canvass on Tuesday, September 25th</a> at 6pm, and Stomp Out Slumlords, one of MDC DSA‚Äôs most thriving campaigns, is organizing to join them. Meet at the LEDC office at 1401 Columbia Road NW, Unit C-1 (the basement) and canvass in neighborhood, where a number of people live at UIP-managed buildings -- one of the biggest offenders for abusing loopholes in rent control laws. <strong>Do you live at a UIP-managed building? We would love to see a </strong><strong>ton</strong><strong> of UIP tenants from across the city at this event.</strong> -- email <a href="mailto:tenants@mdcdsa.org">tenants@mdcdsa.org</a> 
</p>
<p>--Lia R
</p>
<p><em>From Union City yesterday (Thursday) morning:</em>
</p>
<p>													
</p>
<p>Giant settles; Safeway strike possible
</p>
<p>Hundreds of union Safeway employees, members of UFCW Locals 400 and 27, yesterday rallied alongside elected officials, community leaders and other allies, telling management to negotiate a fair contract or face a strike. At the same rally, however, Giant workers announced they had reached a tentative agreement on a new contract, averting a potential work stoppage. ‚ÄúThe promise of a union job was that we won‚Äôt get rich but we will be able to provide health care for our families,‚Äù said Safeway member Jane St. Louis. ‚ÄúBut now, Safeway wants to break that promise.‚Äù Union members will meet on March 5th, announced UFCW 400 president Mark Federici. [The two mega-chains have 25,000 union members in the region.] Giant members will vote on whether to ratify their new collective bargaining agreement, while Safeway members will vote on whether to authorize a strike. ‚ÄúThe countdown starts today,‚Äù Federici said. ‚ÄúThe countdown for justice ends March 5th.‚Äù<a href="http://out02.thedatabank.com/?r=MTAwMg0KSjQxNDY2OC1DMzY2LU0yNjAwNzMtLW13YWNhZG1pbg0KMzcxNTYzNjYxMjMzODMwMDc4ODkzMjYwMDczMTEwDQoxMmIwMDAwMDAyODYzMTENCmh0dHA6Ly93d3cudWZjdzQwMC5vcmcvMjAyMC8wMi8xOS9zYWZld2F5LXdvcmtlcnMtYW5ub3VuY2Utc3RyaWtlLXZvdGUtbWFyY2gtNS8NCnNhZmV3YXl3b3JrZXJzYW5uDQp3b29kbGFuaGFtQGdtYWlsLmNvbQ%3d%3d"> <em>Read more here</em></a> 
</p>
