<p><strong>MDC DSA 4 BERNIE UPDATE</strong>
</p>
<p><strong>--Accomplished! </strong>
</p>
<p><strong>Saturday Feb 15</strong><strong>th </strong><strong> Canvass in East Falls Church</strong> ‚Äì Record number of doors knocked yet! Over 80 volunteers (including Spanish-English bi-lingual folks) knocked on a record-breaking 4,100 doors despite freezing cold temperatures and a technical snafu. Photos<a href="https://twitter.com/Kurtis91H/status/1228859810621329410"> HERE</a>. Afterward we ate, drank, and gabbed at a local beach bar.
</p>
<p>Did you canvass with us and forget to sync your data? You still can on the MiniVan app! Go into the app and tap the cloud+arrow icon in the upper righthand corner of your phone screen.
</p>
<p><strong>Tuesday Feb 18</strong><strong>th</strong><strong> Working Group Meeting</strong>: Nearly thirty (30!) Bernie enthusiasts joined together at the MDC DSA HQ in Dupont Circle to plot our next moves toward putting Bernie in the White House this year. We assigned tasks for upcoming events like the Sat 22nd canvass, GOTV carpooling, 3/3 Super Tuesday Evening Watch Party, and the 3/15 Univision Arizona Dem Debate. 
</p>
<p>Do you want to volunteer for a special role for one of our upcoming events? <em>We need you! </em>Email us at <a href="mailto:DSA4Bernie@mdcdsa.org">DSA4Bernie@mdcdsa.org</a> to find out what roles still need filling!
</p>
