<p><strong>Sat Feb 29</strong><strong>th</strong><strong>: Post-GOTV celebration & South Carolina Election Returns Watch Party!</strong>
</p>
<p>After a full day on the doors talking to Bernie supporters about their Super Tuesday voting plans (see below for info about carpools to canvasses), we deserve food, drink, and fun&hellip;and to watch South Carolina vote for Bernie as their top Democratic choice, and pave the way for Bernie to capture a Super Tuesday victory just days later. 
</p>
<p>We‚Äôll likely meet at Courthaus Social in Clarendon. Please note that it‚Äôs (very!) highly encouraged that you bring proof that you canvassed or phonebanked  that day for Bernie in Virginia!
</p>
<p><strong>&lt;&lt;GET. OUT. THE. VOTE. ü°™ Feb 23-March 3&gt;&gt;</strong>
</p>
<p><strong>Super Tuesday, the largest election day in the primary, is March 3</strong><strong>rd</strong> <strong>in Virginia</strong>. If you haven‚Äôt knocked doors for Bernie in Virginia by then, you‚Äôve officially slept through the revolution. Get Out The Vote, or GOTV, is the ground-game for turning out Bernie supporters to the polls on election day. 
</p>
<p>For GOTV, we are asking people to canvass with the <em>official</em> campaign. <strong>We are organizing carpools for the 29th:</strong> If you need a ride or have a car and can provide rides, please fill out <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfukEyAWvrL03G49TFYuwgXrK0wh3Biqd0NgF5PnnMv0yyOpA/viewform">this form</a> and we‚Äôll plug you into our system. Be sure to recruit your friends to join you! Also, participate in as many other GOTV canvasses as possible. Email us at <a href="mailto:dsa4bernie@mdcdsa.org">dsa4bernie@mdcdsa.org</a> if you have any questions.
</p>
<p><em>Note: We can‚Äôt coordinate with the official campaign behind the scenes, but we </em>can<em> post about their public events. Keep us on the right side of election law and please don‚Äôt share nonpublic info between us and the official campaign!</em>
</p>
